cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper deals with learning hierarchical policies using imitation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus is on options, which are a type of temporal abstraction used in reinforcement learning, making cs.RO a likely category as well. The paper also mentions using visual input in some of the experiments, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses transfer learning and generalization, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
